article.headline: Robert Morris 86, Quinnipiac 68
article.story: CORAOPOLIS, Pa. (AP) -- Tony Lee had 20 points and Jeremy Chappell had 18 to lead Robert Morris to its fourth consecutive win, 86-68 over Quinnipiac on Thursday. Chris Wehye had 17 points for the Bobcats (2-10, 0-3 Northeast Conference), who have lost nine in a row. Derek Coleman had 13 points and a career-high 11 assists and Freddie Harris added 12 points and seven rebounds for the Colonials (9-3, 1-2), who are 6-0 at home this season. Lee added six rebounds, five assists and a game-high six steals. The Colonials led 41-38 at halftime and opened the second half on an 18-0 run and led by as many as 27 with 6:19 to play. The Bobcats missed their first seven shots and committed five turnovers while not scoring during the first 7:18 of the second half. Robert Morris has averaged 82.3 points in its last four games. It was the second-most points Quinnipiac has allowed this season.
